%% Lazy Context Compaction - Solving Token Limit Problem
%% Shows how context is managed across 5-agent workflow

graph TD
    START[👤 User: Campaign Brief] --> PLAN[🎬 Create 5-Step Plan]

    PLAN --> A1[🔍 Agent 1: Brand Strategist<br/>Output: ~2000 tokens]
    A1 --> CTX1[📝 Context: Full output preserved]

    CTX1 --> A2[✍️ Agent 2: Copywriter<br/>Output: ~2500 tokens]
    A2 --> CTX2[📝 Context: Both outputs preserved]

    CTX2 --> A3[🎨 Agent 3: Designer<br/>Output: ~1800 tokens]
    A3 --> CTX3[📝 Context: All 3 outputs preserved]

    CTX3 --> COMPACT{⚠️ Compaction Trigger<br/>After 3 agents}

    COMPACT -->|Summarize older context| SUMMARY[🔄 Gemini Flash Summarization<br/>- Agents 1-2: Summarized ~500 tokens<br/>- Agent 3: Full output preserved]

    SUMMARY --> A4[⭐ Agent 4: Critic<br/>Output: ~1500 tokens<br/>Context: Summary + Agent 3 full]
    A4 --> CTX4[📝 Context: Summary + Agent 3 + Agent 4]

    CTX4 --> A5[📋 Agent 5: Project Manager<br/>Output: ~2000 tokens<br/>Context: Summary + Recent agents full]
    A5 --> FINAL[✅ Complete Campaign<br/>All agents successfully executed]

    style START fill:#ea4335,color:#fff
    style COMPACT fill:#fbbc04,color:#000,stroke:#333,stroke-width:3px
    style SUMMARY fill:#4285f4,color:#fff
    style FINAL fill:#34a853,color:#fff
    style A1 fill:#34a853,color:#fff
    style A2 fill:#34a853,color:#fff
    style A3 fill:#34a853,color:#fff
    style A4 fill:#34a853,color:#fff
    style A5 fill:#34a853,color:#fff

    subgraph "Configuration"
        CONFIG["⚙️ EventsCompactionConfig<br/>- compaction_interval: 3<br/>- overlap_size: 1<br/>- summarizer: Gemini Flash"]
    end

    subgraph "Benefits"
        B1["✅ Prevents token limit failures"]
        B2["✅ Preserves recent context quality"]
        B3["✅ Scales to 10+ agents"]
        B4["✅ Cost efficient"]
    end

    COMPACT -.-> CONFIG
    FINAL -.-> B1 & B2 & B3 & B4
